Pick the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Pop the @lamb mince{200%g} in a #bowl{} with half the mint. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well to combine then shape into burgers, one per person.

> TIP: Make the burgers roughly the same diameter as the bun. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, lay in the lamb burgers and fry until browned and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}, turning occasionally.

> TIP: Adjust the heat if the burgers look like they are browning too fast. IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, drain the @cooked beetroot{250%g} and cut two 1cm thick slices per person. Roughly chop the remainder into small chunks. Roughly chop the @walnuts{20}.

Pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} in a small bowl and stir in the remaining mint. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Halve the @burger buns{2}.

Pop the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} in a bowl with a drizzle of @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @wild rocket{40%g}, walnuts and chopped beetroot. Toss together just before serving.

Spread a little minty yoghurt on the top and base of each bun. Top with the sliced beetroot, minty lamb burger and the bun lid. Serve the burgers alongside the rocket and beetroot salad. Enjoy!